{{Politics of Serbia}}
The '''Democratic Movement of Serbia''' ({{lang-sr|Demokratski pokret Srbije}}) or DEPOS, was a centre-right [[political coalition]] founded in 1992. The coalition was formed by:<ref>http://ius.regione.toscana.it/elezioni/Quaderni/qua56/Saggio3.pdf (in Italian)</ref>
*[[Serbian Renewal Movement]] (SPO) *[[Democratic Party of Serbia]] (DSS) *[[Serbian Liberal Party]] (SLS) *[[Liberals of Serbia|New Democracy]] (ND)
The coalition received 16.89% of the popular vote in the [[Serbian parliamentary election, 1992|1992]] and 16.64% in the [[Serbian parliamentary election, 1993|1993]] parliamentary elections. The DSS left the coalition ahead of the 1993 election, while the DEPOS was joined by the [[Civic Alliance of Serbia]] and the [[People's Peasant Party]]. The coalition was dissolved in 1993 after New Democracy entered into a coalition government with the [[Socialist Party of Serbia|Socialist Party]].
