The '''Garda National Immigration Bureau''' (GNIB; [[Irish language|Irish]]: ''Biúró Náisiúnta an Gharda Síochána um Inimirce'') is a unit of the [[Garda Síochána]], the national police force of [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.garda.ie/Controller.aspx?Page=31&Lang=1|title=Immigration |publisher=An Garda Síochána - Ireland's National Police Service |website=www.garda.ie}}</ref> 

== Duties ==
The GNIB is responsible for the execution of [[deportation]] orders, investigation of [[human trafficking]] complaints, investigation of [[language school]]s, countering [[illegal immigration]] and [[border control]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/421-people-committed-to-prison-in-2016-on-immigration-related-issues-1.3161858 |first=Kitty |last=Holland |date=20 July 2017 |title=421 people committed to prison in 2016 on immigration-related issues|publisher=[[Irish Times]] }}</ref> It also provides support and assistance to local Garda Immigration Officers throughout the State.

== Staff ==
It reports to [[Assistant Commissioner]] John O'Driscoll,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/200-garda-boost-for-specialist-crime-units-436927.html |first=Cormac |last=O'Keeffe |title=200 garda boost for specialist crime units |date=29 December 2016 |publisher=[[Irish Examiner]] }}</ref> and includes two Detective Superintendents, four Detective Inspectors, 24 Detective Sergeants and 180 Detective Gardaí and Gardaí. They are supported by 68 civilian staff. 

The Bureau's headquarters is at 13/14 Burgh Quay, Dublin 2 and it also has offices also at [[Dublin Airport]]. 

