'''Lok Sangharsh Morcha''' (People's Struggle Front) is led by Tarsem Jodhan, a former [[Member of the Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] who had represented the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]] in [[Punjab, India]]. It was formed in 2000.

Its membership comes primarily from brick-kiln workers, rural [[peasant]]s, [[Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act]] workers and [[trade union]] workers.

